### 21.

1\. Now at that time a certain Bhikkhu had committed numerous
Sa*m*ghâdisesa offences, one of which he had concealed for one day, two
for two days, three for three days, \[and so on down to\] and ten for
ten days.

He told, &c.

They told, &c.

'Let then the Sa*m*gha, O Bhikkhus, impose upon that Bhikkhu an
inclusive probation equal in duration to the longest time during which
he has concealed any one or more of those offences <span
id="fr_736"></span>[1](#fn_715.md).'

\[Then follows the kammavâ*k*â as before.\]

